#forms

group the mixins for form elements, these can be used directly from your own selectors or through the mars-build-form, for these examples the selectors created by mars-build-forms are being used

##variables

There is a set of variables in default-variable that allow you to modify some properties of these mixins and not have to rewrite them for small adjustments

~~~scss
$form-element-bg: $white;
$form-element-border-radius: 3px;
$form-element-border: 1px solid $border-color;
$form-element-disabled: .3;
$form-element-icon-color: $primary;
$form-element-line-height: 1.8em;
$form-element-padding: .4em 1em;
$form-element-placeholder: rgba($font-color, .4);
~~~

##form-element

This mixin generates the styles of the common parts of most form elements, it is used by the @extend %form-element.

since
: 1.0.0

extend
: `%form-element`

used by:
: [input](#input)
: [textarea](#textarea)
: [select](#select)
: [input-search](#input-search)

<% example_tabs do %>

~~~scss
@mixin form-element {
  display: block;
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 100%;
  padding: $form-element-padding;
  font-size: inherit;
  line-height: $form-element-line-height;
  background: $white none no-repeat calc(100% - .7em) center;
  background-size: 1em;
  border: $form-element-border;
  border-radius: $form-element-border-radius;
  transition: background .2s ease-out, border .2s ease-out;
  appearance: none;

  &:focus {
    @extend %focus;
  }

  &::placeholder {
    color: $form-element-placeholder;
    opacity: 1; // Firefox's bug https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/pull/11526
  }

  &:disabled,
  &.is-disabled {
    pointer-events: none;
    opacity: $form-element-disabled;
  }
}
~~~

