##form-checks

This mixin generates the styles of the common parts of most form elements, it is used by the @extend %form-checks.

since
: 1.0.0

extend
: <%= link_to '%form-checks', '/documentation/extends' %>

used by:
: [checkbox](#checkbox)
: [radio](#radio)

<% example_tabs do %>
~~~scss
@mixin form-checks {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-bottom: .5em;
  cursor: pointer;

  & + & {
    margin-left: .5em;
  }

  &[disabled],
  &.is-disabled {
    cursor: not-allowed;
    opacity: $form-element-disabled;
  }
}
~~~

~~~css
.checkbox, .radio {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-bottom: .5em;
  cursor: pointer; }
  [disabled].checkbox, [disabled].radio, .is-disabled.checkbox, .is-disabled.radio {
    cursor: not-allowed;
    opacity: 0.3; }
~~~
<% end %>


